Just some of the legislation from the past three years: CA Senate SB249 defeated in 2012 NY state SAFE Act passed in 2013 CA state LIFE Act in 2013 Federal S.150 in defeated in 2013 CA SB808 """"Ghost Gun"""" ban CA SB53 Ammunition background check and purchase permit CA SB1016 Firearm seizure warrants California already has a standing """"assault weapon"""" ban. Not only does the law define what is illegal, but what is *LEGAL*. Now politicians have claimed that the exemption in the Penal Code, which they wrote and voted into law, is a """"loophole"""". So, firearm owners who supported the ban because they did not own or want the firearms in question and wanted to make a compromise, were now being rewarded by seeing their own firearms added to the ban. All semiauto rifles with detachable magazines almost got banned in California last year, if not for the Governor's veto. During the SB249 push in 2012, the chief of staff for the bill's author stated in social media that after semiautos were outlawed they would pursue bans on bolt-actions and pump shotguns. """"No one wants to take your guns."""" Yeah, sure. """"These aren't the droids you're looking for.""""
